                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "A problem with programmers is that we want to turn our notations into programming languages.  A virtue of a good notation as a tool for thought is that you choose to ignore some details, allow for some ambiguity.  It's a natural programmer tendency to consider this laziness.  I can imagine my 20 year younger self thinking exactly this."
